    • Method Detail

      • mvcGroupInit

        void mvcGroupInit(@Nonnull
                  Map<String,Object> args)
        Post initialization callback.

        This callback is called for all artifacts that belong to the same MVC group right after each instance has been created. Each entry on the args Map points either to an MVC member or a variable that was defined using any of the createMVCGroup and/or createMVC methods that can take a Map as parameter.

        Parameters:
        args - a Map of MVC instances or variables keyed by type.

      • mvcGroupDestroy

        void mvcGroupDestroy()
        Callback for when the group is destroyed and disposed from the application.

        Once an artifact has been "destroyed" it should not be used anymore. The application will remove any references to the group on its cache.
